# 00 Baseline Controls

## Intent
Set non-negotiable defaults for privacy, security, and compliance across `ctf/`.

## Mandatory
- Deny by default: new processing is blocked until purpose, lawful basis, data class, and retention class are defined.
- Privacy by default: minimum data collection and least permissive user defaults.
- Least privilege by default for users, services, and operators.
- Encryption in transit and at rest for all personal data and PHI.
- Structured logging only; no raw personal data in logs, traces, crash reports, or analytics.
- All data access paths must produce auditable events with actor, action, purpose, target, and timestamp.

## Prohibited
- Shipping features without data inventory tags.
- Reusing data for incompatible purposes without re-authorization/legal basis.
- Using production personal data in dev/test environments.
- Direct client-side access to sensitive stores without server policy enforcement.

## Required Evidence
- Feature-level privacy/security checklist.
- Data-flow entry in processing record.
- Risk entry for unresolved controls.
